Epix IPTV Review [15K+ Live TV, 60K+ VOD, 36-Hour Free Trial]

With over a year in the IPTV space, Epix IPTV provides access to 15,000+ live channels and a large on-demand catalog featuring 60,000+ movies and TV shows, including sports and international content.

The service comes with a 36-hour free trial and supports its custom app, but I tested it using TiviMate and IPTV Smarters Pro, which both worked without issues.

Pricing starts at $14.99/month, with additional plans available for 3 and 6 months. The service works on all major devices, including FireStick, Android TV, and smart TVs,  using Xtream Codes or M3U login.

Also, as Epix IPTV is an unverified service, its highly recommended to use a VPN to protect your privacy, avoid ISP throttling, and keep your streaming activity safe.

Does Epix IPTV offer a Free Trial?

Yes, Epix IPTV offers a 36-hour free trial to test all live channels and streaming speed. Just visit the website and submit your email through the chatbot.

Official Website of Epix IPTV

While searching for Epix IPTV, I found several websites with similar names that confuse you.

To ensure youre opting for the correct service that I reviewed, always verify the URL www.epixiptv.com before subscribing. I added the screenshot above to confirm youre on the right website.

How to Get EPIX IPTV

Setting up Epix IPTV is simple. I tested it on my FireStick, but you can follow the same steps on any compatible device, such as Android Phones/TV, NVIDIA Shield, or others.

1. Get the Free Trial/Subscription

Step 1: Visit www.epixiptv.com on your laptop/PC/mobile, go to the chat section, and submit your username and email to receive your free trial details.

Step 2: Youll receive your free trial details via email shortly. If it doesnt appear in your inbox, be sure to check your spam folder.

Step 3: Visit the Epix IPTV website, select your preferred plan (Monthly, Quarterly, etc.), enter your device details, and complete the order to activate your subscription.

You will receive all the login details (Xtreme Code OR M3U Links) in your email.

2. Choose The IPTV Player

Epix IPTV also offers its custom APK, which you can install with downloader code/URL 5872808 or tinyurl.com/ythtcwey on the Downloader app. After installation, log in with your credentials and start streaming.

Epix IPTV is an unverified service, using a VPN is essential to ensure secure and uninterrupted streaming while protecting your privacy.

What Can I watch on EPIX IPTV?

Heres a quick overview of what Epix IPTV offers:

1. Live TV

Epix IPTV gives you access to 15,000+ live channels covering every major genre all organized with proper EPG support and easily accessible through IPTV players like TiviMate and IPTV Smarters Pro.

Youll get top-tier entertainment with channels like HBO, AMC, FX, Bravo, MBC Action, Rotana Cinema, ARY Digital, and Hum TV, plus fan favorites like Star Plus, Colors, Zee TV, and other global entertainment giants.

For sports fans, theres broad coverage from ESPN, Sky Sports, beIN Sports, BT Sport, TSN, and dedicated event channels for football, cricket, UFC, boxing, NBA, and F1.

News channels include CNN, Fox News, BBC News, Al Jazeera, and other top sources. The kids section is solid too, with Disney, Cartoon Network, Nickelodeon, and more.

Whats unique is the inclusion of fitness and lifestyle channels like Z Living, Beachbody On Demand, FitFusion, and Health TV, perfect for home workouts and wellness.

Some dummy or inactive channels do exist, which is common with large IPTV lineups, but the core channels worked well and most streamed in HD or better.

2. Movies & TV Shows

Epix IPTV offers a 60,000+ title VOD library loaded with movies, series, and international content. Categories are separated by genre and region, making browsing simple.

Youll find everything from Hollywood blockbusters and Netflix originals to European cinema, Korean dramas, and Bollywood films.

The VOD section is regularly updated, I found recent action releases alongside classics, plus dedicated categories for kids, and documentaries.

3. PAY-PER-VIEW

Epix IPTV includes a dedicated PPV section featuring major events like UFC fights, WWE pay-per-views, and top boxing matchups. Channels such as PPV UFC, MMA, and Wrestling go live only during scheduled events, delivering real-time access when it matters most.

Is EPIX IPTV Legal & Safe to Use?

Epix IPTV is an unverified IPTV service, so its important to exercise caution, especially with increased monitoring of unofficial platforms in some regions.

We scanned the Epix IPTV APK file with VirusTotal (see screenshot above), and no malicious threats were found during the scan.

Even if the scan appears clean, unverified services may still pose privacy risks, it can be tracked by your ISPs, which can lead to constant IPTV buffering. Therefore, using a reliable VPN like Surfshark is recommended.

How is EPIX IPTVs Customer Support?

Epix IPTV advertises 24/7 free VIP support, but my experience didnt quite match that promise.

Theres no live chat or real-time support on their website just a form that collects your email. While they do offer support through WhatsApp and email, I found the email response was slow, and there was no immediate help available when I needed it.

Overall, the support felt basic and delayed, not what youd expect from a VIP service.

EPIX IPTV IPTV is compatible with?

FAQs

Does Epix IPTV offer a free trial?

Yes, Epix IPTV offers a 36-hour free trial so you can test the service before subscribing.

How many connections does Epix IPTV support?

Epix IPTV allows only one connection per subscription. Extra connections may require additional charges.

Is Epix IPTV a legal service?

No, Epix IPTV is an unverified IPTV service.

Is EPIX IPTV Worth It?

Epix IPTV delivers a good overall experience, offering a wide range of live channels, VOD content, and a functional EPG, which worked great during testing. The streaming quality is decent, and the content variety is solid.

However, I cant fully recommend it the customer support is slow, and the websites user experience is poor, with broken navigation and a frustrating user experience.

The $14.99/month pricing feels high, especially considering platforms like Z2U that offer more channels & a bigger VOD library.

The 36-hour free trial does give some flexibility to try the service. However, its an unverified IPTV service, so its important to use a VPN like Surfshark for privacy.
